Sentiment Analysis of The Times Music Reviews¶

Part IV: Data Visualization of VADER Sentiment Analyzer Scores¶

How have artforms been reported? Is there a status hierarchy between them? How has this changed over time?

  • Project: What counts as culture? Reporting and criticism in The Times 1785-2000
  • Project Team: Dave O'Brien (lead), Lucy Havens (Jupyter Notebook author), Orian Brooke, Mark Taylor
  • Funding: from the Centre for Data, Culture & Society, University of Edinburgh
  • Dataset: 83,625 reviews about music published in The Times from 1950 through 2009 from The Times Archive

Begun February 2021

Table of Contents¶

  2. Analyze the Data

In [13]:
def termFilter(term_string, dataframe):
    df_terms = list(dataframe.term)
    with_term = []
    for t in df_terms:
        if term_string in t:
            with_term += [True]
        else:
            with_term += [False]
    
    assert(len(with_term) == len(df_terms))
    return with_term

with_opera = termFilter(" opera", df)

In [23]:
# Create a DataFrame with the compound, positive, and negative scores for a given genre
def makeScoreDataFrame(df_genre):
    df_scores = pd.DataFrame({"identifier":list(df_genre["identifier"]), "compound":list(df_genre["compound"]), 
                        "positive":list(df_genre["positive"]), "neutral":list(df_genre["neutral"]), 
                        "negative":list(df_genre["negative"]), "year":list(df_genre["year"])})
    df_scores.set_index("identifier", inplace=True)
    return df_scores

# Create one DataFrame per decade of data
# We'll do this for four genres, so let's write a function to avoid re-writing code!
def plotScoresByDecade(vader, genre):
    vader_1950s = vader[(vader.year < 1960)]
    vader_1960s = vader[(vader["year"] >= 1960) & (vader["year"] < 1970)]
    vader_1970s = vader[(vader["year"] >= 1970) & (vader["year"] < 1980)]
    vader_1980s = vader[(vader["year"] >= 1980) & (vader["year"] < 1990)]
    vader_1990s = vader[(vader["year"] >= 1990) & (vader["year"] < 2000)]
    vader_2000s = vader[(vader["year"] >= 2000)]
    scores = ["compound", "positive", "neutral", "negative"]
    for score in scores:
        sns.set_context("paper")
        fig, ax = plt.subplots(2,3, sharex=False, sharey=False, figsize=(16,10))
        fig.suptitle("VADER "+str(score.capitalize())+" Scores of The Times Reviews with Term '"+genre.capitalize()+"' by Decade", fontsize=14)
        fig.tight_layout(pad=5)
        if score == "compound":
            y_min, y_max = -1, 1
        else:
            y_min, y_max = 0, 1
        sns.scatterplot(ax=ax[0,0], x=vader_1950s["year"], y=vader_1950s[score], color=color_dict[score], alpha=.7)
        ax[0,0].set(title=score.capitalize()+" Scores in 1950s", xlim=(1949,1960), ylim=(y_min, y_max))
        sns.scatterplot(ax=ax[0,1], x=vader_1960s["year"], y=vader_1960s[score], color=color_dict[score], alpha=.7)
        ax[0,1].set(title=score.capitalize()+" Scores in 1960s", xlim=(1959,1970), ylim=(y_min, y_max))
        sns.scatterplot(ax=ax[0,2], x=vader_1970s["year"], y=vader_1970s[score], color=color_dict[score], alpha=.7)
        ax[0,2].set(title=score.capitalize()+" Scores in 1970s", xlim=(1969,1980), ylim=(y_min, y_max))
        sns.scatterplot(ax=ax[1,0], x=vader_1980s["year"], y=vader_1980s[score], color=color_dict[score], alpha=.7)
        ax[1,0].set(title=score.capitalize()+" Scores in 1980s", xlim=(1979,1990), ylim=(y_min, y_max))
        sns.scatterplot(ax=ax[1,1], x=vader_1990s["year"], y=vader_1990s[score], color=color_dict[score], alpha=.7)
        ax[1,1].set(title=score.capitalize()+" Scores in 1990s", xlim=(1989,2000), ylim=(y_min, y_max))
        sns.scatterplot(ax=ax[1,2], x=vader_2000s["year"], y=vader_2000s[score], color=color_dict[score], alpha=.7)
        ax[1,2].set(title=score.capitalize()+" Scores in 2000s", xlim=(1999,2010), ylim=(y_min, y_max))

        sns.set_style("ticks")
        sns.despine(left=True, trim=False)
        plt.show()
        
        fig.savefig("SentimentCharts/vader_"+score+"_by_decade_"+genre+".png")
